The 21-year-old is aiming to clinch the top scorer’s award in the ongoing Kriss Darlin Super Cup in Kibra, Nairobi, to prove wrong those who have doubted his capability to excel on the pitch due to his weight.Having won the award in the two previous editions, Shirao believes a third one in a row will see those who have looked down upon him before, because of his body size, change their perspective. Little-known Gogo Boys FC striker Hillary Shirao is a man on a mission.
The 21-year-old is aiming to clinch the top scorer’s award in the ongoing Kriss Darlin Super Cup in Kibra, Nairobi, to prove wrong those who have doubted his capability to excel on the pitch due to his weight.
Having won the award in the two previous editions, Shirao believes a third one in a row will see those who have looked down upon him before, because of his body size, change their perspective.



